AGI - The Gip of the Tribunal of Florence, at the request of the District Anti-Mafia and Anti-terrorism of the Tuscan capital, issued an order of precaution against three persons for the crimes of corruption for an act contrary to the duties of office and abusive access to a computer or telematic system. The measure concerns a superior officer of the Carabinieri in service in Prato> (destinator of the custody in prison), investigated - as well as for the crimes of corruption by act contrary to the duties of office, abusive access to a computer system> or telematic also for pawned, omitted denunciation of crime to the judicial authority and for omission of office acts, a textile entrepreneur and the owner of a private investigators agency. The measures were carried out by the Carabinieri ROS in the provinces of Prato and Turin, > with the support of the local provincial commands of Carabinieri.
The investigation focused on the conduct of the officer of the Arma, who, in his capacity as Commander of Reparto, would have entertained corrupt relations with the entrepreneur, placing multiple acts contrary to the duties of office, also consisted in abusive access to the database of police forces. In the face of this, the military would have obtained from the entrepreneur economic usefulness (payment of a trip to the United States) and reassurances about an interest, through a political exponent of his knowledge, to avoid the transfer of the officer to another seat, which did not draw the hoped effect.
In addition, the officer would have entertained corrupt relations with a holder of an investigative agency, to which he would first disclosed news about his own employee destined to remain confidential and, then, he would have procacciato clients receiving, as a consideration, utility of different nature. The investigations - which would have evidenced a considerable search for accreditation by the officer at the Italian and Chinese entrepreneurship - have documented further access to the database of the Police Forces executed by the military (at least 99 have been identified), with the aim, among other things, to provide information to another Prato entrepreneur and to people with whom he engaged reports of personal knowledge, as well as interventions in other public offices to know the state of interest. The general command of the Carabinieri started the transfer procedures to another location and could start the procedures for possible removal from the Arma.&nbsp;

